President Donald J. Trump had his first meeting with Pope Francis and Cardinal Secretary of State Pietro Parolin. The focus of their discussions was on combating terrorism and how religious communities can help alleviate human suffering in crisis regions like Syria, Libya, and ISIS-controlled areas. They also emphasized the shared values of the United States and the Holy See in promoting human rights, combating human suffering, protecting religious freedom, and fighting global famine. The United States announced over $300 million in anti-famine spending, specifically targeting Yemen, South Sudan, Somalia, and Nigeria.